race.comment: DAISYDOO (3) has been knocking on the door all prep, placing in all four runs back and beaten a head in her past two. She's at peak fitness now on the quick back-up and only needs to hold her form to be winning. BRISTLER (1) folded after leading in what has turned out to be a strong form race. Freshened with a month between runs and capable of bouncing back sharply. If left alone in front he can pinch it. PANTOJA (5) gave supporters a sight when resuming, only to tire late. He'll be better for that hit-out and has jumped out well since. Expect a stronger showing. ROUND TWO (7) returns from a short break and draws to get every favour. Her peak ratings measure up nicely for this level and she's an appealing each-way hope.
